notes: --- TEST 1: Strings vs Comments ---
notes: The lexer should NOT treat these as comments because they are inside quotes.
print "He left some notes: on the table."
print "Type start_notes: to begin your story."
print "Always remember your end_notes!"

notes: --- TEST 2: Same-line block comment ---
notes: The lexer should skip the comment but successfully read 'd is 100'.
start_notes: quick secret end_notes d is 100

notes: --- TEST 3: Comment keywords inside other comments ---
notes: The single line comment should ignore the 'end_notes' keyword below.
notes: remember to type end_notes later!


start_notes: 
  I love using notes: it is so much fun!
  The multi-line comment should ignore the 'notes:' keyword above.
end_notes


notes: --- TEST 4: Keyword Boundaries ---
notes: These should be parsed as variables, not comments.
my_notes: is 50
my_start_notes: is 100


notes: --- TEST 5:Error flow ---
notes: the first 'end_notes' will close the comment, and the next line will cause an error.
start_notes:
   We are hiding this whole block
   start_notes: 
     this was an older note 
   end_notes
   is this line still hidden? 
end_notes